g.text: Visual Calculus: The white ceramic cuirass hugs your torso, shielding your vitals without adding much bulk to your form...
Perception (Hearing): Your movements cause tiny little clicks, like dice rolling somewhere far away, as the plates reorient to your motions.
Visual Calculus: Certainly, but you may want to hold on to the armour you have for long enough to properly analyse it, figure out its vulnerabilities.
Visual Calculus: Remember, this is a highly specialized kinetic re-distributor meant to stop bullets. Wear it, observe its properties. See if there's a *weakness* in the design.
Half Light: For the day you have to *fight* someone covered in the same material.
Visual Calculus: The hardened vitreous enamel, at once sleek and voluptuous, adds a glow to your cheeks and a spring to your step. Just imagine what a full suit of this stuff could do for you!
Visual Calculus: The hardened vitreous enamel, at once sleek and light, adds a glow to your cheeks and a spring to your step. Just imagine what a full suit of this stuff could do for you!
Visual Calculus: Two? Are you sure you're correct there? There was a helmet too. Three pieces more like. You were *ambitious*.
You: I remember a feeling -- being worried about crossing paths with someone in this armour.
You: This is the long sought after *enemy technology*. I can't just enjoy it -- I must *study* it.
You: Yeah, I *want* the full suit!
Visual Calculus: Well, it's a bit late to think about all this now, isn't it?
You: Better late than never, huh?
Visual Calculus: As you fold your fingers into a fist, you realize you could knock anyone out with one punch... the white ceramic gloves wrap around your digits comfortably.
Visual Calculus: Then you should prepare -- analyse this armour, figure out its vulnerabilities.
You: This gear could line my pockets with cash. I could probably sell it to some other cops.
Visual Calculus: Well, you found that one piece you were after, anyway. Don't forget to enjoy it!
Visual Calculus: Remember, the vitreous enamel material acts as a kinetic re-distributor. It's meant to stop bullets. Wear it, observe its properties. See if there's a *weakness* in the design.
You: One down -- two pieces to go. Here I come.
You: This is the long sought after *enemy technology*. I can't just enjoy it -- I must *study* it.
Visual Calculus: It may be a while before you have all the pieces. In the meantime, you should analyse the armour, figure out its vulnerabilities.
Visual Calculus: Yes. You should analyse the armour, figure out its vulnerabilities.
Visual Calculus: You look down at the white ceramic sabatons hugging your arches and calves, surprised at how well they fit.
Composure: You really do feel more confident. Invulnerability does that. Even partial invulnerability.
You: It is good to be an unstoppable ceramic man.
You: Decked out in future-armour. Like a cop ought to be.
Composure: You really do feel more confident. Invulnerability does that. Even partial invulnerability.
Visual Calculus: As your head is ensconced in the ceramic helm, you realize --
You: I will be responsible with this. This is just to protect me from harm, not to show off.
